npc/sinta: The portal ahead leads to Stage 4 — the gambling platform itself. The inside of the machine.
npc/sinta: Everything you have seen until now was just the delivery system. The ads, the spam, the phishing, the debt enforcement — all of it existed to funnel people into what is through that portal.
npc/sinta: I have been to the edge of it. I could not go further.
npc/sinta: It looks like a casino. Bright lights. No windows. No clocks. Designed so that nothing inside it reminds you that time exists outside.
npc/sinta: The slot machines run continuously. They have no jackpot — the jackpot is a display. The odds are set by the algorithm itself, and they always, always favor the house.
npc/sinta: You will see things in there that are designed to make you stop moving forward. Animations. Numbers. Near-wins. The same psychology used on the people playing from the outside.
npc/sinta: Do not engage with any of it. Keep your eyes on the source signal.
npc/sinta: The Collector will not follow you past this point — her jurisdiction ends at the network boundary. What waits past the portal is the House's own domain.
npc/sinta: One more thing. In the real world, if you or someone you know is struggling with gambling: call 119 extension 8. They will not judge you. They will help.
npc/sinta: Now go. You are almost there.
